{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"94a274fe-2cec-4495-a081-16f0a791dfb6","content":"Here's how to migrate your Azure DevOps pipeline from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n## 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd/update these packages in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.2\" />\n```\n\nRemove the old split packages (`MSTest.TestAdapter`, `MSTest.TestFramework`) — the unified `MSTest` meta-package replaces them.\n\n## 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\nReplace:\n\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nWith `dotnet test` (MTP uses the `dotnet` CLI directly):\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests (MTP)'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --\n      --report-trx\n      --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n## Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | MTP |\n|---|---|---|\n| Test runner | vstest.console.exe | Built into test host |\n| TRX reports | Automatic | `--report-trx` flag + TrxReport package |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` flag + CodeCoverage package |\n| Publishing | Handled by task | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` / `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` tasks |\n\nThe `condition: always()` on `PublishTestResults@2` ensures results are published even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"afbc6271-9b21-4281-8ec5-49755b189beb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":695,"requestId":"67CB:2636C7:2B009B0:2F499A6:69FD34A8"},"id":"a38581eb-1cc9-4377-84e7-49d4b73ec844","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:21.673Z","parentId":"68e41cf2-ae06-4ada-a945-ae634a28f3ed"}
